Text: CLINTON: Thank you, Jim.
Speech: Thank you, Jim.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And thank you to the people of Hartford, our hosts.
Speech: And thank you to the people of Hartford, our hosts.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I want to begin by saying again how much I respect Senator Dole and his record of public service and how hard I will try to make this campaign and this debate one of ideas, not insults.
Speech: I want to begin by saying again how much I respect Senator Dole and his record of public service and how hard I will try to make this campaign and this debate one of ideas, not insults.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Four years ago I ran for president at a time of high unemployment and rising frustration.
Speech: Four years ago I ran for president at a time of high unemployment and rising frustration.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I wanted to turn this country around with a program of opportunity for all, responsibility from all, and an American community where everybody has a role to play.
Speech: I wanted to turn this country around with a program of opportunity for all, responsibility from all, and an American community where everybody has a role to play.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I wanted a government that was smaller and less bureaucratic to help people make the most of their own lives.
Speech: I wanted a government that was smaller and less bureaucratic to help people make the most of their own lives.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Four years ago you took me on faith.
Speech: Four years ago you took me on faith.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Now there's a record: Ten and a half million more jobs, rising incomes, falling crime rates and welfare rolls, a strong America at peace.
Speech: Now there's a record: Ten and a half million more jobs, rising incomes, falling crime rates and welfare rolls, a strong America at peace.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Let's keep it going.
Speech: Let's keep it going.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We cut the deficit by 60 percent.
Speech: We cut the deficit by 60 percent.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Now, let's balance the budget and protect Medicare, Medicaid, education and the environment.
Speech: Now, let's balance the budget and protect Medicare, Medicaid, education and the environment.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We cut taxes for 15 million working Americans.
Speech: We cut taxes for 15 million working Americans.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Now let's pass the tax cuts for education and child rearing, help with medical emergencies, and buying a home.
Speech: Now let's pass the tax cuts for education and child rearing, help with medical emergencies, and buying a home.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We passed family and medical leave.
Speech: We passed family and medical leave.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Now let's expand it so more people can succeed as parents and in the work force.
Speech: Now let's expand it so more people can succeed as parents and in the work force.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We passed 100,000 police, the assault weapons ban, the Brady Bill.
Speech: We passed 100,000 police, the assault weapons ban, the Brady Bill.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Now let's keep going by finishing the work of putting the police on the street and tackling juvenile gangs.
Speech: Now let's keep going by finishing the work of putting the police on the street and tackling juvenile gangs.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We passed welfare reform.
Speech: We passed welfare reform.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Now let's move a million people from welfare to work.
Speech: Now let's move a million people from welfare to work.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And most important, let's make education our highest priority so that every eight-year-old will be able to read, every 12-year-old can log onto the Internet, every 18-year-old can go to college.
Speech: And most important, let's make education our highest priority so that every eight-year-old will be able to read, every 12-year-old can log onto the Internet, every 18-year-old can go to college.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We can build that bridge to the 21st Century.
Speech: We can build that bridge to the 21st Century.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And I look forward to discussing exactly how we're going to do it.
Speech: And I look forward to discussing exactly how we're going to do it.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Thank you, Mr. President, for those kind words.
Speech: Thank you, Mr. President, for those kind words.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Thank the people of Hartford, the Commission, and all those out here who may be listening or watching.
Speech: Thank the people of Hartford, the Commission, and all those out here who may be listening or watching.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: It's a great honor for me to be here standing here as the Republican nominee.
Speech: It's a great honor for me to be here standing here as the Republican nominee.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I'm very proud to be the Republican nominee reaching out to Democrats and Independents.
Speech: I'm very proud to be the Republican nominee reaching out to Democrats and Independents.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I have three very special people with me tonight: My wife, Elizabeth; my daughter, Robin, who has never let me down, and a fellow named Frank Carafa from New York, along with Ollie Manninen who helped me out in the mountains of Italy a few years back.
Speech: I have three very special people with me tonight: My wife, Elizabeth; my daughter, Robin, who has never let me down, and a fellow named Frank Carafa from New York, along with Ollie Manninen who helped me out in the mountains of Italy a few years back.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I've learned from them that people do have tough times.
Speech: I've learned from them that people do have tough times.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: And sometimes you can't go it alone.
Speech: And sometimes you can't go it alone.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: And that's what America is all about.
Speech: And that's what America is all about.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I remember getting my future back from doctors and nurses and a doctor in Chicago named Dr. Kalikian .
Speech: I remember getting my future back from doctors and nurses and a doctor in Chicago named Dr. Kalikian .
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: And ever since that time, I've tried to give something back to my country, to the people who are watching us tonight.
Speech: And ever since that time, I've tried to give something back to my country, to the people who are watching us tonight.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: America is the greatest place on the face of the earth.
Speech: America is the greatest place on the face of the earth.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Now, I know millions of you still have anxieties.
Speech: Now, I know millions of you still have anxieties.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: You work harder and harder to make ends meet and put food on the table.
Speech: You work harder and harder to make ends meet and put food on the table.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: You worry about the quality and the safety of your children, and the quality of education.
Speech: You worry about the quality and the safety of your children, and the quality of education.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: But even more importantly, you worry about the future and will they have the same opportunities that you and I have had.
Speech: But even more importantly, you worry about the future and will they have the same opportunities that you and I have had.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: And Jack Kemp and I want to share with you some ideas tonight.
Speech: And Jack Kemp and I want to share with you some ideas tonight.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Jack Kemp is my running mate, doing an outstanding job.
Speech: Jack Kemp is my running mate, doing an outstanding job.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Now, I'm a plain-speaking man and I learned long ago that your word was your bond.
Speech: Now, I'm a plain-speaking man and I learned long ago that your word was your bond.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: And I promise you tonight that I'll try to address your concerns and not try to exploit them.
Speech: And I promise you tonight that I'll try to address your concerns and not try to exploit them.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: It's a tall order, but I've been running against the odds for a long time and, again, I'm honored to be here this evening.
Speech: It's a tall order, but I've been running against the odds for a long time and, again, I'm honored to be here this evening.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: CLINTON: Well, Jim, I believe that the Federal government should give people the tools and try to establish the conditions in which they can make the most of their own lives.
Speech: Well, Jim, I believe that the Federal government should give people the tools and try to establish the conditions in which they can make the most of their own lives.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: That, to me, is the key.
Speech: That, to me, is the key.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And that leads me to some different conclusions from Senator Dole.
Speech: And that leads me to some different conclusions from Senator Dole.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: For example, we have reduced the size of the Federal government to its smallest size in 30 years.
Speech: For example, we have reduced the size of the Federal government to its smallest size in 30 years.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We reduced more regulations, eliminated more programs than my two Republican predecessors.
Speech: We reduced more regulations, eliminated more programs than my two Republican predecessors.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: But I have worked hard for things like the Family and Medical Leave Law, the Brady Bill, the assault weapons ban, the program to put 100,000 police on the street.
Speech: But I have worked hard for things like the Family and Medical Leave Law, the Brady Bill, the assault weapons ban, the program to put 100,000 police on the street.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: All of these are programs that Senator Dole opposed that I supported, because I felt they were a legitimate effort to help people make the most of their own lives.
Speech: All of these are programs that Senator Dole opposed that I supported, because I felt they were a legitimate effort to help people make the most of their own lives.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I've worked hard to help families impart values to their own children.
Speech: I've worked hard to help families impart values to their own children.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I supported the V-chip so that parents would be able to control what their kids watch on television when they're young, along with the ratings systems for television and educational television.
Speech: I supported the V-chip so that parents would be able to control what their kids watch on television when they're young, along with the ratings systems for television and educational television.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I supported strong action against the tobacco companies to stop the marketing, advertising, and sale of tobacco to young people.
Speech: I supported strong action against the tobacco companies to stop the marketing, advertising, and sale of tobacco to young people.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I supported a big increase in the safe and drug-free schools program.
Speech: I supported a big increase in the safe and drug-free schools program.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: These were areas on which Senator Dole and I differed, but I believed they were the right areas for America to be acting together as one country to help individuals and families make the most of their own lives and raise their kids with good values and a good future.
Speech: These were areas on which Senator Dole and I differed, but I believed they were the right areas for America to be acting together as one country to help individuals and families make the most of their own lives and raise their kids with good values and a good future.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: DOLE: I think the basic difference is, and I have had some experience in this, I think the basic difference, I trust the people.
Speech: I think the basic difference is, and I have had some experience in this, I think the basic difference, I trust the people.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: The President trusts the government.
Speech: The President trusts the government.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: We go back and look at the healthcare plan that he wanted to impose on the American people.
Speech: We go back and look at the healthcare plan that he wanted to impose on the American people.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: One seventh the total economy, 17 new taxes, price controls, 35 to 50 new bureaucracies that cost $1.5 trillion.
Speech: One seventh the total economy, 17 new taxes, price controls, 35 to 50 new bureaucracies that cost $1.5 trillion.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Don't forget that, that happened in 1993.
Speech: Don't forget that, that happened in 1993.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: A tax increase, a tax on everybody in America.
Speech: A tax increase, a tax on everybody in America.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Not just the rich.
Speech: Not just the rich.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: If you made 25,000 as the original proposal, you got your Social Security taxes increased.
Speech: If you made 25,000 as the original proposal, you got your Social Security taxes increased.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: We had a BTU tax we turned into a $35 million gas tax, a $265 billion tax increase.
Speech: We had a BTU tax we turned into a $35 million gas tax, a $265 billion tax increase.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I guess I rely more on the individual.
Speech: I guess I rely more on the individual.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I carry a little card in my pocket called the Tenth Amendment.
Speech: I carry a little card in my pocket called the Tenth Amendment.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Where possible, I want to give power back to the states and back to the people.
Speech: Where possible, I want to give power back to the states and back to the people.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: That's my difference with the President.
Speech: That's my difference with the President.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: We'll have specific differences later.
Speech: We'll have specific differences later.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: He noted a few, but there are others.
Speech: He noted a few, but there are others.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: CLINTON: I trust the people.
Speech: I trust the people.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We've done a lot to give the people more powers to make their own decisions over their own lives.
Speech: We've done a lot to give the people more powers to make their own decisions over their own lives.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: But I do think we are right when we try to, for example, give mothers and newborns 48 hours before they can be kicked out of the hospital, ending these drive-by deliveries.
Speech: But I do think we are right when we try to, for example, give mothers and newborns 48 hours before they can be kicked out of the hospital, ending these drive-by deliveries.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I think we were right to pass the Kassebaum-Kennedy bill, which says you can't lose your health insurance just because you change jobs or because someone in your family's been sick.
Speech: I think we were right to pass the Kassebaum-Kennedy bill, which says you can't lose your health insurance just because you change jobs or because someone in your family's been sick.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Our government is smaller and less bureaucratic and has given more authority to the states than its two predecessors under Republican presidents.
Speech: Our government is smaller and less bureaucratic and has given more authority to the states than its two predecessors under Republican presidents.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: But I do believe we have to help our people get ready to succeed in the 21st Century.
Speech: But I do believe we have to help our people get ready to succeed in the 21st Century.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: DOLE: Well, he's better off than he was four years ago.
Speech: Well, he's better off than he was four years ago.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: CLINTON: I agree with that.
Speech: I agree with that.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: That's right.
Speech: That's right.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: DOLE: And I may be better off four years from now, but I don't know.
Speech: And I may be better off four years from now, but I don't know.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I looked at the slowest growth in the century.
Speech: I looked at the slowest growth in the century.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: He inherited a growth of 4.7 4.8 percent, now it's down to about 2.4 percent.
Speech: He inherited a growth of 4.7 4.8 percent, now it's down to about 2.4 percent.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: We're going to pass a million bankruptcies this year for the first time in history.
Speech: We're going to pass a million bankruptcies this year for the first time in history.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: We've got stagnant wages.
Speech: We've got stagnant wages.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: In fact, women's wages have dropped 2.2 percent.
Speech: In fact, women's wages have dropped 2.2 percent.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Men's wages haven't gone up, gone down.
Speech: Men's wages haven't gone up, gone down.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: So we have stagnation.
Speech: So we have stagnation.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: We have the highest foreign debt in history.
Speech: We have the highest foreign debt in history.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: And it seems to me that if you take a look, are you better off?
Speech: And it seems to me that if you take a look, are you better off?
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Well, I guess some may be better off.
Speech: Well, I guess some may be better off.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Saddam Hussein is probably better off than he was four years ago.
Speech: Saddam Hussein is probably better off than he was four years ago.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Renee Proval (ph) is probably better off than he was four years ago.
Speech: Renee Proval (ph) is probably better off than he was four years ago.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: But are the American people?
Speech: But are the American people?
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: They're working harder and higher and harder paying more taxes.
Speech: They're working harder and higher and harder paying more taxes.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: For the first time in history, you pay about 40 percent of what you earn.
Speech: For the first time in history, you pay about 40 percent of what you earn.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: More than you spend for food, clothing and shelter combined for taxes under this administration.
Speech: More than you spend for food, clothing and shelter combined for taxes under this administration.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: So some may be better off.
Speech: So some may be better off.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: They talk about family income being up.
Speech: They talk about family income being up.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: That's not true in Connecticut, family income is down.
Speech: That's not true in Connecticut, family income is down.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: And it's up in some cases because both parents are working.
Speech: And it's up in some cases because both parents are working.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: One works for the family, and one works to pay taxes for the government.
Speech: One works for the family, and one works to pay taxes for the government.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: We're going to give them tax cuts so they can spend more time with their children, maybe even take a vacation.
Speech: We're going to give them tax cuts so they can spend more time with their children, maybe even take a vacation.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: That's what America is all about.
Speech: That's what America is all about.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: CLINTON: Well, let me say, first of all, in February Senator Dole acknowledged that the American economy was in the best shape it's been in in 30 years.
Speech: Well, let me say, first of all, in February Senator Dole acknowledged that the American economy was in the best shape it's been in in 30 years.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We have ten and a half million more jobs, a faster job growth rate than under any Republican administration since the 1920s.
Speech: We have ten and a half million more jobs, a faster job growth rate than under any Republican administration since the 1920s.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Wages are goings up for the first time in a decade.
Speech: Wages are goings up for the first time in a decade.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We have record numbers of new small businesses.
Speech: We have record numbers of new small businesses.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We have the biggest drop in the number of people in poverty in 27 years.
Speech: We have the biggest drop in the number of people in poverty in 27 years.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: All groups of people are growing.
Speech: All groups of people are growing.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We had the biggest drop in income inequality in 27 years in 1995.
Speech: We had the biggest drop in income inequality in 27 years in 1995.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: The average family's income has gone up over $1600 just since our economic plan passed.
Speech: The average family's income has gone up over $1600 just since our economic plan passed.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: So I think it's clear that we're better off than we were four years ago.
Speech: So I think it's clear that we're better off than we were four years ago.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Now we need to focus on what do we need to do to be better off still.
Speech: Now we need to focus on what do we need to do to be better off still.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: How can we help people as we are to get their retirements when they work for small businesses, to be able to afford health insurance, to be able to educate their children.
Speech: How can we help people as we are to get their retirements when they work for small businesses, to be able to afford health insurance, to be able to educate their children.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: That's what I want to focus on.
Speech: That's what I want to focus on.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: But we are clearly better off than we were four years ago, as Senator Dole acknowledged this year.
Speech: But we are clearly better off than we were four years ago, as Senator Dole acknowledged this year.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: DOLE: I doubt that I acknowledged that this year.
Speech: I doubt that I acknowledged that this year.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: But in any event, I think we just look at the facts.
Speech: But in any event, I think we just look at the facts.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: We ask the people that are viewing tonight, are you better off than you were four years ago.
Speech: We ask the people that are viewing tonight, are you better off than you were four years ago.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: It's not whether we're better off, it's whether they're better off.
Speech: It's not whether we're better off, it's whether they're better off.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Are you working harder to put food on the table, feed your children.
Speech: Are you working harder to put food on the table, feed your children.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Are your children getting a better education.
Speech: Are your children getting a better education.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Drug use has doubled the past 44 months all across America.
Speech: Drug use has doubled the past 44 months all across America.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Crime has gone down but it's because the mayors like Rudy Giuliani where one third of the drop happened in one city, New York City.
Speech: Crime has gone down but it's because the mayors like Rudy Giuliani where one third of the drop happened in one city, New York City.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: So, yes, some may be better off.
Speech: So, yes, some may be better off.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: But of the people listening tonight, the working families who will benefit from economic packages, they'll be better off when Bob Dole is president and Jack Kemp is vice president.
Speech: But of the people listening tonight, the working families who will benefit from economic packages, they'll be better off when Bob Dole is president and Jack Kemp is vice president.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: CLINTON: Absolutely not.
Speech: Absolutely not.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Let's look at the position.
Speech: Let's look at the position.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: First of all, remember that in this campaign season, since Senator Dole's been a candidate, he has bragged about the fact that he voted against Medicare in the beginning, in 1965, one of only 12 members.
Speech: First of all, remember that in this campaign season, since Senator Dole's been a candidate, he has bragged about the fact that he voted against Medicare in the beginning, in 1965, one of only 12 members.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: He said he did the right thing then, he knew it wouldn't work at the time.
Speech: He said he did the right thing then, he knew it wouldn't work at the time.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: That's what he said.
Speech: That's what he said.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Then his budget that he passed along with Speaker Gingrich cut Medicare $270 billion, more than was necessary to repair the Medicare trust fund.
Speech: Then his budget that he passed along with Speaker Gingrich cut Medicare $270 billion, more than was necessary to repair the Medicare trust fund.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It would have charged seniors more for out-of-pocket costs as well as more in premiums because doctors could have charged them more.
Speech: It would have charged seniors more for out-of-pocket costs as well as more in premiums because doctors could have charged them more.

Speech: It took three and a half years.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Speech: It wasn't until election year, Mr. President, that you ever thought about stopping smoking.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: So after Speaker Gingrich and Senator Dole took over the Congress, I went to New Hampshire and a man suggested -- a gentleman that unfortunately just passed away a couple of days ago, suggested that we appoint a commission.
Speech: So after Speaker Gingrich and Senator Dole took over the Congress, I went to New Hampshire and a man suggested -- a gentleman that unfortunately just passed away a couple of days ago, suggested that we appoint a commission.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And then Senator Dole's ardent supporters, Senator McCain, who's out there today, along with Senator Feingold, supported, sponsored a campaign finance reform proposal.
Speech: And then Senator Dole's ardent supporters, Senator McCain, who's out there today, along with Senator Feingold, supported, sponsored a campaign finance reform proposal.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I strongly supported it.
Speech: I strongly supported it.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And members of Senator Dole's own party in the Senate killed it.
Speech: And members of Senator Dole's own party in the Senate killed it.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And he was not out there urging them to vote for the McCain-Feingold bill.
Speech: And he was not out there urging them to vote for the McCain-Feingold bill.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: So I think the American people, including the Perot supporters, know that I have had a consistent record in favor of campaign finance reform, and I will continue to have.
Speech: So I think the American people, including the Perot supporters, know that I have had a consistent record in favor of campaign finance reform, and I will continue to have.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And I hope we can finally get it in the next session of Congress, because we need it badly.
Speech: And I hope we can finally get it in the next session of Congress, because we need it badly.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: DOLE: Well, on campaign reform itself, we're going to get it when we have a bipartisan commission, take it out of politics.
Speech: Well, on campaign reform itself, we're going to get it when we have a bipartisan commission, take it out of politics.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Get people who don't have any interest in politics but understand the issue and let them make the recommendation to Congress.
Speech: Get people who don't have any interest in politics but understand the issue and let them make the recommendation to Congress.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Now, we're now kidding anybody, Mr. President.
Speech: Now, we're now kidding anybody, Mr. President.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Speech: These are sophisticated people watching tonight.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Name: Robert J. Dole

Name: Robert J. Dole

Speech: They know the Democratic party won't do it.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Speech: We ought to agree that somebody else should do it.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: And we have to vote it up or down, Mr. President.
Speech: And we have to vote it up or down, Mr. President.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: CLINTON: Well, Jim, I think every American in any position of responsibility should be concerned about what's happened.
Speech: Well, Jim, I think every American in any position of responsibility should be concerned about what's happened.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I am.
Speech: I am.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: But let's look at the overall record.
Speech: But let's look at the overall record.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Overall in America cocaine use has dropped 30 percent in the last four years, casual drug use down 13 percent.
Speech: Overall in America cocaine use has dropped 30 percent in the last four years, casual drug use down 13 percent.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: The tragedy is that our young people are still increasing their use of drugs up to about 11 percent total with marijuana, and I regret it.
Speech: The tragedy is that our young people are still increasing their use of drugs up to about 11 percent total with marijuana, and I regret it.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Speech: Let me tell you what I tried to do about it.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I appointed a four-star general who led our efforts south of the border to keep drugs from coming into the country as our nation's drug czar.
Speech: I appointed a four-star general who led our efforts south of the border to keep drugs from coming into the country as our nation's drug czar.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: The most heavily directed, decorated solder in uniform when he retired.
Speech: The most heavily directed, decorated solder in uniform when he retired.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We submitted the biggest drug budget ever.
Speech: We submitted the biggest drug budget ever.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We have dramatically increased control and enforcement at the border.
Speech: We have dramatically increased control and enforcement at the border.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We supported a a crime bill that had 60 death penalties including, including the death penalty for drug kingpins.
Speech: We supported a a crime bill that had 60 death penalties including, including the death penalty for drug kingpins.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And I supported a big expansion in safe and drug-free schools program to support things like the DARE program because I thought all those things were very important.
Speech: And I supported a big expansion in safe and drug-free schools program to support things like the DARE program because I thought all those things were very important.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Do I think that I bear some responsibility for the fact that too many of our children still don't understand drugs are wrong, drugs can kill you.
Speech: Do I think that I bear some responsibility for the fact that too many of our children still don't understand drugs are wrong, drugs can kill you.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Even though I have consistently opposed the legalization of drugs all my public life and worked hard against them.
Speech: Even though I have consistently opposed the legalization of drugs all my public life and worked hard against them.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I think we all do.
Speech: I think we all do.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And I hope we can do better.
Speech: And I hope we can do better.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I don't think this issue should be politicized because my record is clear and I don't think Senator Dole supports using using drugs.
Speech: I don't think this issue should be politicized because my record is clear and I don't think Senator Dole supports using using drugs.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I think we just have to continue to work on this until those who think it isn't dangerous and won't kill them and won't destroy their lives, get the message and change.
Speech: I think we just have to continue to work on this until those who think it isn't dangerous and won't kill them and won't destroy their lives, get the message and change.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Speech: Again, well it's, you are very selective, Mr. President.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: You don't want to politicize drugs, but it's already politicized Medicare, go out and scare senior citizens and other vulnerable groups, veterans and people who get Pell Grants and things like this.
Speech: You don't want to politicize drugs, but it's already politicized Medicare, go out and scare senior citizens and other vulnerable groups, veterans and people who get Pell Grants and things like this.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Speech: I mean, you say we've done all these bad things, which isn't the case.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Name: Robert J. Dole

Speech: The record is pretty clear in Arkansas, when you were governor.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Speech: You resisted the appointment of a drug czar there because you thought it might interfere with treatment.

Speech: You cut interdiction substantially.

Speech: I mean that's what, I want to stop it from coming across the border.

Speech: This is a invasion of drugs from all over the world.

Speech: Is that the kind of leadership we need?

Speech: And I won't comment on other things that happened in your administration or your past about drugs.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Speech: But it seems to me the kids ought to -- if they've started, they ought to stop and just don't do it.

Speech: Let me say again, we did have a drug czar in Arkansas, but he answered to the governor, just like this one answers to the President.

Speech: That's what I thought we ought to do.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Name: Robert J. Dole

Name: Robert J. Dole

Name: Robert J. Dole

Speech: He didn't succeed and I signed it and I'm glad I did.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Name: Robert J. Dole

Speech: I believe that we have to do these things with a government that's smaller and less bureaucratic, but that we have to do them nonetheless.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It's inconvenient for Senator Dole, but the truth is I've reduced the size of government more than my Republican predecessors.
Speech: It's inconvenient for Senator Dole, but the truth is I've reduced the size of government more than my Republican predecessors.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And I did stop them, I admit that.
Speech: And I did stop them, I admit that.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I sure stopped their budget.
Speech: I sure stopped their budget.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Their budget cut enforcement for the Environmental Protection Agency by a third.
Speech: Their budget cut enforcement for the Environmental Protection Agency by a third.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It cut funds to clean up toxic waste dumps with 10 million of our kids still living within four miles of a toxic waste dump, by a third.
Speech: It cut funds to clean up toxic waste dumps with 10 million of our kids still living within four miles of a toxic waste dump, by a third.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It ended the principle that the polluters should pay for those toxic waste dumps unless it was very recent.
Speech: It ended the principle that the polluters should pay for those toxic waste dumps unless it was very recent.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Their budget weakened our support for education.
Speech: Their budget weakened our support for education.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: $30 billion, even cut funds for scholarships and college loans.
Speech: $30 billion, even cut funds for scholarships and college loans.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Their budget cut $270 billion in Medicare and, finally, their budget withdrew the national guarantee of healthcare to poor children, families with children with handicaps, the elderly in nursing homes, poor pregnant women.
Speech: Their budget cut $270 billion in Medicare and, finally, their budget withdrew the national guarantee of healthcare to poor children, families with children with handicaps, the elderly in nursing homes, poor pregnant women.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It was wrong for the country and calling it conservative won't make it right.
Speech: It was wrong for the country and calling it conservative won't make it right.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It was a bad decision for America and would have been bad for our future if I hadn't stopped it.
Speech: It was a bad decision for America and would have been bad for our future if I hadn't stopped it.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: DOLE: Well, the President can define himself in any way he wants, but I think we have to look at the record.
Speech: Well, the President can define himself in any way he wants, but I think we have to look at the record.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Go back to the time he was, what, Texas director for George McGovern.
Speech: Go back to the time he was, what, Texas director for George McGovern.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: George McGovern is a friend of mine, so I don't mean, but he was a liberal, proud liberal.
Speech: George McGovern is a friend of mine, so I don't mean, but he was a liberal, proud liberal.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I've just finished reading a book, I think it's called -- what is it called, what is it, The Demise of the Democratic Party by Ronald Cardash (ph) or something talking about all the liberal influences in the administration.
Speech: I've just finished reading a book, I think it's called -- what is it called, what is it, The Demise of the Democratic Party by Ronald Cardash (ph) or something talking about all the liberal influences in the administration.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Whether it's organized labor or whether it's the Hollywood elite or whether some of the media elite or whether it's the labor unions or whatever.
Speech: Whether it's organized labor or whether it's the Hollywood elite or whether some of the media elite or whether it's the labor unions or whatever.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: And so I think you take a look at it.
Speech: And so I think you take a look at it.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: The bottom line is this: I think the American people, thought he'd recite all these bills and all these things, they want to know what's going to happen to them.
Speech: The bottom line is this: I think the American people, thought he'd recite all these bills and all these things, they want to know what's going to happen to them.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: They've all got a lot of anxieties out there.
Speech: They've all got a lot of anxieties out there.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Did anybody complain when you raised taxes?
Speech: Did anybody complain when you raised taxes?
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Did anybody go out and ask the people, how are you going to pay the extra money?
Speech: Did anybody go out and ask the people, how are you going to pay the extra money?
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: That's why we want an economic package.
Speech: That's why we want an economic package.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: We want the government to pinch their pennies for a change instead of the people pinching their pennies.
Speech: We want the government to pinch their pennies for a change instead of the people pinching their pennies.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: That's what our message is to the people watching.
Speech: That's what our message is to the people watching.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Not all this back and forth, you voted this way, you voted that way, we want a better America as we go into the next century.
Speech: Not all this back and forth, you voted this way, you voted that way, we want a better America as we go into the next century.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: CLINTON: The way you get a better America is to balance the budget and protect Medicare, Medicaid, education and the environment; to give a targeted tax cut -- and let me talk about the education tax cut -- to let people have a $10,000 deduction for the cost of college tuition in any year, any kind of college tuition; to give families a tax credit, a dollar for dollar reduction in their taxes for the cost of a typical community college so we can open that to everybody.
Speech: The way you get a better America is to balance the budget and protect Medicare, Medicaid, education and the environment; to give a targeted tax cut -- and let me talk about the education tax cut -- to let people have a $10,000 deduction for the cost of college tuition in any year, any kind of college tuition; to give families a tax credit, a dollar for dollar reduction in their taxes for the cost of a typical community college so we can open that to everybody.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And then to let people save in an IRA and withdraw from it without a tax penalty for education, home buying or medical expenses, that's the right way to go into the 21st Century, balance the budget and cut taxes, not balloon with this $550 billion tax scheme.
Speech: And then to let people save in an IRA and withdraw from it without a tax penalty for education, home buying or medical expenses, that's the right way to go into the 21st Century, balance the budget and cut taxes, not balloon with this $550 billion tax scheme.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: DOLE: Let me say first, on the President's promise for another tax cut.
Speech: Let me say first, on the President's promise for another tax cut.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I mean, I've told people as I've traveled around, all of you that got the tax cut he promised last time, vote for him in '96 and not many hands go up.
Speech: I mean, I've told people as I've traveled around, all of you that got the tax cut he promised last time, vote for him in '96 and not many hands go up.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: So the question is, would you buy a used election promise from my opponent.
Speech: So the question is, would you buy a used election promise from my opponent.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: The people want economic reform.
Speech: The people want economic reform.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: They're having a hard time making ends meet.
Speech: They're having a hard time making ends meet.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: You've got one parent working for the government, the other parent working for the family.
Speech: You've got one parent working for the government, the other parent working for the family.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: This is about getting the economy moving again.
Speech: This is about getting the economy moving again.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: This is about American jobs and opportunities.
Speech: This is about American jobs and opportunities.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: It's about the government, as I said before, pinching its pennies for a change instead of the poor taxpayer.
Speech: It's about the government, as I said before, pinching its pennies for a change instead of the poor taxpayer.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: When they raise your taxes nobody runs around asking people where are you going to get the extra money.
Speech: When they raise your taxes nobody runs around asking people where are you going to get the extra money.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I think the government can do better.
Speech: I think the government can do better.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Are there personal differences?
Speech: Are there personal differences?
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: DOLE: Well, my blood pressure is lower, my weight, my cholesterol, but I will not make health an issue in this campaign.
Speech: Well, my blood pressure is lower, my weight, my cholesterol, but I will not make health an issue in this campaign.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: So I think he's a bit taller than I am.
Speech: So I think he's a bit taller than I am.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: But I think there are personal differences.
Speech: But I think there are personal differences.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I mean, I'm not I don't like to get into personal matters.
Speech: I mean, I'm not I don't like to get into personal matters.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: As far as I'm concerned, this is a campaign about issues.
Speech: As far as I'm concerned, this is a campaign about issues.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: It's about my vision for America and about his liberal vision for America.
Speech: It's about my vision for America and about his liberal vision for America.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: And not about personal things.
Speech: And not about personal things.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: You know, I think his liberal vision is a thing of the past.
Speech: You know, I think his liberal vision is a thing of the past.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I know he wants to disown it.
Speech: I know he wants to disown it.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I wouldn't want to be a liberal either, Mr. President, but you're stuck with it because that's your record, that's your record in Arkansas: The biggest tax increase in history.
Speech: I wouldn't want to be a liberal either, Mr. President, but you're stuck with it because that's your record, that's your record in Arkansas: The biggest tax increase in history.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: The biggest crime increase in history, the biggest drug increase in history in Arkansas.
Speech: The biggest crime increase in history, the biggest drug increase in history in Arkansas.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: CLINTON: Well, just for the record, when I was governor we had the lowest -- second lowest tax burden of any state in the country, the highest job growth rate of any state when I ran for president and were widely recognized for a lot of other advances.
Speech: Well, just for the record, when I was governor we had the lowest -- second lowest tax burden of any state in the country, the highest job growth rate of any state when I ran for president and were widely recognized for a lot of other advances.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: But the important thing is, what are we going to do now.
Speech: But the important thing is, what are we going to do now.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I think a targeted tax cut is better for our future, targeted to education and child rearing, with the rest of the education plan, hooking up all of our classrooms to the Internet by the year 2000.
Speech: I think a targeted tax cut is better for our future, targeted to education and child rearing, with the rest of the education plan, hooking up all of our classrooms to the Internet by the year 2000.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Making sure we've got an army of reading volunteers, trained people to teach with parents and teachers so that our eight year olds can learn to read.
Speech: Making sure we've got an army of reading volunteers, trained people to teach with parents and teachers so that our eight year olds can learn to read.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Investing in our environment.
Speech: Investing in our environment.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Cleaning up two-thirds of the worst toxic waste dumps.
Speech: Cleaning up two-thirds of the worst toxic waste dumps.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Those plans are better than this $550 billion tax scheme.
Speech: Those plans are better than this $550 billion tax scheme.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Now, remember, folks, even Senator Dole's campaign co-chair here, Senator D'Amato, says he's got to cut Medicare to pay for this.
Speech: Now, remember, folks, even Senator Dole's campaign co-chair here, Senator D'Amato, says he's got to cut Medicare to pay for this.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Everybody who's looked at it, 500 economists, seven Nobel prize winners, say it's bad for the economy.
Speech: Everybody who's looked at it, 500 economists, seven Nobel prize winners, say it's bad for the economy.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It's going to blow a hole in the deficit It's going to raise taxes on nine million people and require bigger cuts than the one I vetoed.
Speech: It's going to blow a hole in the deficit It's going to raise taxes on nine million people and require bigger cuts than the one I vetoed.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Our plan is better, it will take us into the future with a growing economy and healthier families.
Speech: Our plan is better, it will take us into the future with a growing economy and healthier families.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: DOLE: Well, I'm really encouraged to know of your renewed friendship with Al D'Amato, and I know he appreciates it.
Speech: Well, I'm really encouraged to know of your renewed friendship with Al D'Amato, and I know he appreciates it.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: You didn't even have tax cuts in your budget, Mr. President, the first two years you were president.
Speech: You didn't even have tax cuts in your budget, Mr. President, the first two years you were president.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: It wasn't until we had a Republican Congress you even thought about, you talked about tax cuts.
Speech: It wasn't until we had a Republican Congress you even thought about, you talked about tax cuts.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Getting back to personal differences, I think, Jim, if you are a little more specific, but I think the President could clarify one thing tonight and that's the question of pardons.
Speech: Getting back to personal differences, I think, Jim, if you are a little more specific, but I think the President could clarify one thing tonight and that's the question of pardons.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I know you talked about it on the Jim, with Jim Lehrer on the PBS show.
Speech: I know you talked about it on the Jim, with Jim Lehrer on the PBS show.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: And I've never discussed Whitewater, as I've told you personally.
Speech: And I've never discussed Whitewater, as I've told you personally.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I'm not discussing Whitewater now.
Speech: I'm not discussing Whitewater now.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: But I am discussing the power the President has to grant pardons.
Speech: But I am discussing the power the President has to grant pardons.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: And hopefully in the next segment you could lay that to rest.
Speech: And hopefully in the next segment you could lay that to rest.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: CLINTON: Well, first of all, you know, he made that remark about Senator D'Amato.
Speech: Well, first of all, you know, he made that remark about Senator D'Amato.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: He's arranged for me to spend a lot more time with Senator D'Amato in the last couple years so I'm more familiar with his comments than I used to be.
Speech: He's arranged for me to spend a lot more time with Senator D'Amato in the last couple years so I'm more familiar with his comments than I used to be.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Let me say what I've said already about this pardon issue.
Speech: Let me say what I've said already about this pardon issue.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: This is an issue they've brought up.
Speech: This is an issue they've brought up.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: It's under, there's been no consideration of it, no discussion of it.
Speech: It's under, there's been no consideration of it, no discussion of it.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I will tell you this: I will not give anyone special treatment and I will strictly adhere to the law.
Speech: I will tell you this: I will not give anyone special treatment and I will strictly adhere to the law.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And that is what every president has done, as far as I know, in the past but what every other president's has done.
Speech: And that is what every president has done, as far as I know, in the past but what every other president's has done.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: This is something I take seriously and that's my position.
Speech: This is something I take seriously and that's my position.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: DOLE: But it seems to me the president shouldn't have any comment at all.
Speech: But it seems to me the president shouldn't have any comment at all.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Particularly where it's someone where you've had business dealings.
Speech: Particularly where it's someone where you've had business dealings.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I mean, you may be sending a signal.
Speech: I mean, you may be sending a signal.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I don't know, I'm not questioning anybody.
Speech: I don't know, I'm not questioning anybody.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: But as a President of the United States, when somebody asks you about pardons, you say no comment, period.
Speech: But as a President of the United States, when somebody asks you about pardons, you say no comment, period.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: And I think he made a mistake.
Speech: And I think he made a mistake.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: And I think when you make a mistake, you say I made a mistake.
Speech: And I think when you make a mistake, you say I made a mistake.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: But apparently his position hasn't changed.
Speech: But apparently his position hasn't changed.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: If there are other specific areas, but beyond that I haven't gotten into any of these things, as the President knows.
Speech: If there are other specific areas, but beyond that I haven't gotten into any of these things, as the President knows.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: We've had that discussion.
Speech: We've had that discussion.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: And again I know Senator D'Amato I think may have had a hearing or two on Whitewater, I can't remember, but he's not my general chairman, he's a friend of mine.
Speech: And again I know Senator D'Amato I think may have had a hearing or two on Whitewater, I can't remember, but he's not my general chairman, he's a friend of mine.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: And so is Senator Kennedy a friend of yours.
Speech: And so is Senator Kennedy a friend of yours.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: CLINTON: You bet.
Speech: You bet.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: DOLE: I remember one day on the floor I said now, gentlemen, let me tax your memories, and Kennedy jumped up and said, why haven't we thought of that before.
Speech: I remember one day on the floor I said now, gentlemen, let me tax your memories, and Kennedy jumped up and said, why haven't we thought of that before.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: You know, so one of your liberal friends.
Speech: You know, so one of your liberal friends.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: CLINTON: No comment.
Speech: No comment.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: DOLE: What's the subject matter?
Speech: What's the subject matter?
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: DOLE: See, if I say anything it's going to be misconstrued.
Speech: See, if I say anything it's going to be misconstrued.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I don't think there is even a race between the two, it's about our vision for America.
Speech: I don't think there is even a race between the two, it's about our vision for America.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I happen to like President Clinton personally.
Speech: I happen to like President Clinton personally.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I'm addressing him all evening as Mr. President.
Speech: I'm addressing him all evening as Mr. President.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I said in 1992 he didn't extend that courtesy to President Bush.
Speech: I said in 1992 he didn't extend that courtesy to President Bush.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: But I respect the presidency.
Speech: But I respect the presidency.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I've served under a number of presidents.
Speech: I've served under a number of presidents.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: They all have their strengths and they all have their weaknesses.
Speech: They all have their strengths and they all have their weaknesses.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: So I'd rather talk about my strengths.
Speech: So I'd rather talk about my strengths.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: And I think I have my strengths and I think the best thing going for Bob Dole is that Bob Dole keeps his word.
Speech: And I think I have my strengths and I think the best thing going for Bob Dole is that Bob Dole keeps his word.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: It's a question between trust and fear, and I would say, I think, Mr. President, about all you've got going in this campaign is fear.
Speech: It's a question between trust and fear, and I would say, I think, Mr. President, about all you've got going in this campaign is fear.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: You're spending millions and millions of dollars in negative ads frightening senior citizens.
Speech: You're spending millions and millions of dollars in negative ads frightening senior citizens.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I know this to be a fact because I had one tell me last week, Senator don't cut my Medicare.
Speech: I know this to be a fact because I had one tell me last week, Senator don't cut my Medicare.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I'm trying to save your Medicare, just as I rescued Social Security with a bipartisan commission.
Speech: I'm trying to save your Medicare, just as I rescued Social Security with a bipartisan commission.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I have relatives on Medicare.
Speech: I have relatives on Medicare.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I used to sign welfare checks for my grandparents.
Speech: I used to sign welfare checks for my grandparents.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I know all about poverty and all about need and all about taking care of people, and that's been my career in the United States Senate.
Speech: I know all about poverty and all about need and all about taking care of people, and that's been my career in the United States Senate.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: And I'll keep my word on the economic package.
Speech: And I'll keep my word on the economic package.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: If I couldn't cut taxes and balance the budget the same time, I wouldn't look at you in the eye in your living room or wherever you might be and say that this is good for America.
Speech: If I couldn't cut taxes and balance the budget the same time, I wouldn't look at you in the eye in your living room or wherever you might be and say that this is good for America.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: People will tell you who served with Bob Dole, agree or disagree, he kept his word.
Speech: People will tell you who served with Bob Dole, agree or disagree, he kept his word.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: That's what this race is all about.
Speech: That's what this race is all about.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: CLINTON: I'd like the American people to know that I have worked very hard to be on their side.
Speech: I'd like the American people to know that I have worked very hard to be on their side.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And to move this country forward and we're better off than we were four years ago.
Speech: And to move this country forward and we're better off than we were four years ago.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: But the most important thing is my plan for the 21st Century is a better plan.
Speech: But the most important thing is my plan for the 21st Century is a better plan.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: A targeted tax cut, a real commitment to educational reform.
Speech: A targeted tax cut, a real commitment to educational reform.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: A deep commitment to making welfare reform work with incentives to the private sector to move people from welfare to work.
Speech: A deep commitment to making welfare reform work with incentives to the private sector to move people from welfare to work.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Now we have to create those jobs, now that we're requiring people to go do work.
Speech: Now we have to create those jobs, now that we're requiring people to go do work.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: A commitment to continuing step-by-step healthcare reform with the next step helping people who are between jobs to access healthcare and not lose it just because they are out of work for a while.
Speech: A commitment to continuing step-by-step healthcare reform with the next step helping people who are between jobs to access healthcare and not lose it just because they are out of work for a while.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: A commitment to grow the economy while protecting the environment.
Speech: A commitment to grow the economy while protecting the environment.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: That's what I'd like them to know about me; that I've gotten up every day and worked for the American people and worked so that their children could have their dreams come true.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And I like, I like Senator Dole, you can probably tell we like each other.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: As I said, I've worked all my life when I was in the Congress.
Speech: As I said, I've worked all my life when I was in the Congress.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I left on June 11th because I wanted the American people to know that I was willing to give up something.
Speech: I left on June 11th because I wanted the American people to know that I was willing to give up something.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: President Clinton ran for governor in 1990 and said he's going to fill out his term, but he didn't.
Speech: President Clinton ran for governor in 1990 and said he's going to fill out his term, but he didn't.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: He's president so I guess it's a little better deal.
Speech: He's president so I guess it's a little better deal.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: But I wanted the American people to know I was willing to give up something.
Speech: But I wanted the American people to know I was willing to give up something.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I wasn't just getting more power and more power.
Speech: I wasn't just getting more power and more power.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: So I rolled the dice, I put my career on the line because I really believe the future of America is on the line.
Speech: So I rolled the dice, I put my career on the line because I really believe the future of America is on the line.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: We can give you all these numbers, they don't mean a thing.
Speech: We can give you all these numbers, they don't mean a thing.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: If you are out of work, you have nothing to eat or you can't have medical care, or you're holding a crack baby in your arms right now, what do you do next?
Speech: If you are out of work, you have nothing to eat or you can't have medical care, or you're holding a crack baby in your arms right now, what do you do next?

Name: Robert J. Dole

Speech: You know, America's best days are ahead of us.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I've seen the tough times, I know they can be better and I'll lead America to a brighter future.
Speech: I've seen the tough times, I know they can be better and I'll lead America to a brighter future.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: CLINTON: Let's look at that.
Speech: Let's look at that.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: When I ran for president, I said we'd cut the deficit in half in four years; we cut it by 60 percent.
Speech: When I ran for president, I said we'd cut the deficit in half in four years; we cut it by 60 percent.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I said that our economic plan would produce eight million jobs, we have ten and a half million new jobs.
Speech: I said that our economic plan would produce eight million jobs, we have ten and a half million new jobs.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We're number one in autos again, record numbers of new small businesses.
Speech: We're number one in autos again, record numbers of new small businesses.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I said we'd put, pass a crime bill that would put 100,000 police on the street, ban assault weapons, and deal with the problems that ought to be dealt with with capital punishment, including capital punishment for drug kingpins, and we did that.
Speech: I said we'd put, pass a crime bill that would put 100,000 police on the street, ban assault weapons, and deal with the problems that ought to be dealt with with capital punishment, including capital punishment for drug kingpins, and we did that.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I said we would change the way welfare works, and even before the bill passed we'd moved nearly two million people from welfare to work, working with states and communities.
Speech: I said we would change the way welfare works, and even before the bill passed we'd moved nearly two million people from welfare to work, working with states and communities.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I said we'd get tougher with child support and child support enforcement's up 50 percent.
Speech: I said we'd get tougher with child support and child support enforcement's up 50 percent.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I said that I would work for tax relief for middle class Americans.
Speech: I said that I would work for tax relief for middle class Americans.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: The deficit was bigger than I thought it was going to be.
Speech: The deficit was bigger than I thought it was going to be.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I think they're better off, all of us are, that we got the interest rates down and the deficit down.
Speech: I think they're better off, all of us are, that we got the interest rates down and the deficit down.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Republicans talk about it, but we're the first the first administration in anybody's lifetime looking at this program to bring that deficit down four years in a row.
Speech: Republicans talk about it, but we're the first the first administration in anybody's lifetime looking at this program to bring that deficit down four years in a row.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: We still gave tax cuts to 15 million working Americans, and now I've got a plan that's been out there for two years, it could have been passed already, but instead the Republicans shut the government down to try to force their budget and their plan on me, and I couldn't take that.
Speech: We still gave tax cuts to 15 million working Americans, and now I've got a plan that's been out there for two years, it could have been passed already, but instead the Republicans shut the government down to try to force their budget and their plan on me, and I couldn't take that.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: But we'll get the rest of that tax relief.
Speech: But we'll get the rest of that tax relief.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And so I think when you look at those results, you know the plan I've laid out for the future has a very good chance of being enacted if you'll give me a chance to build that bridge to the 21st Century.
Speech: And so I think when you look at those results, you know the plan I've laid out for the future has a very good chance of being enacted if you'll give me a chance to build that bridge to the 21st Century.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: DOLE: Well, there he goes again, that line has been used before, I mean, exaggerating all the things that he did.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: Let's take all these four years in a row.
Speech: Let's take all these four years in a row.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: He came in with a high growth rate, the 1990 budget agreement, which some, you know, didn't like, had some very tough cost controls, put a lot of pressure on Congress.
Speech: He came in with a high growth rate, the 1990 budget agreement, which some, you know, didn't like, had some very tough cost controls, put a lot of pressure on Congress.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Name: Robert J. Dole

Speech: And he cut defense an extra $60 billion, threw a lot of people out of work.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Speech: He talks about a smaller government.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Speech: There are actually more people in government except for people in defense related jobs.

Speech: The government's bigger than it was when President Kennedy was around, even though he says it's not.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Speech: In addition, Republican Congress cut $53 billion.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Speech: Governor Engler of Michigan cut taxes 21 times, created a lot of new jobs.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: When I'm President of the United States we're going to have a governors' council and we're going to work directly with the governors to get power back to the people and back to the states.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: But I believe that my plan is better than Senator Dole's ill-advised $550 billion scheme which I'll say again will blow a hole in the deficit.
Speech: But I believe that my plan is better than Senator Dole's ill-advised $550 billion scheme which I'll say again will blow a hole in the deficit.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Speech: Our plan will balance the budget, grow the economy, preserve the environment, and invest in education.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Speech: We have the right approach for the future and looks at the results.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Speech: It is not midnight in America, Senator.
