Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: CLINTON: Well, first, Jim, let me thank you and thank you, Senator Dole, and thank you, ladies and gentlemen, all of you listening tonight for the chance you've given us to appear.
Speech: Well, first, Jim, let me thank you and thank you, Senator Dole, and thank you, ladies and gentlemen, all of you listening tonight for the chance you've given us to appear.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I want to say in the beginning that I am profoundly grateful for the chance that you have given me to serve as president for the last four years.
Speech: I want to say in the beginning that I am profoundly grateful for the chance that you have given me to serve as president for the last four years.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I never could have dreamed anything like this would come my way in life, and I've done my best to be faithful to the charge you've given me.
Speech: I never could have dreamed anything like this would come my way in life, and I've done my best to be faithful to the charge you've given me.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I'm proud of the fact that America is stronger and more prosperous and more secure than we were four years ago.
Speech: I'm proud of the fact that America is stronger and more prosperous and more secure than we were four years ago.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And I'm glad we're going in the right direction.
Speech: And I'm glad we're going in the right direction.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And I've done my best tonight to lay out my plans for going forward to an even better future in the next century.
Speech: And I've done my best tonight to lay out my plans for going forward to an even better future in the next century.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I'd like to leave you with the thought that the things I do as president are basically driven by the people whose lives I have seen affected by what does or doesn't happen in this country.
Speech: I'd like to leave you with the thought that the things I do as president are basically driven by the people whose lives I have seen affected by what does or doesn't happen in this country.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: The auto worker in Toledo who was unemployed when I was elected and now has a great job because we're number one in auto production again.
Speech: The auto worker in Toledo who was unemployed when I was elected and now has a great job because we're number one in auto production again.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: All the people I've met who used to be on welfare who are now working and raising their children.
Speech: All the people I've met who used to be on welfare who are now working and raising their children.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: And I think what others could do for our country and themselves if we did the welfare reform thing in the proper way.
Speech: And I think what others could do for our country and themselves if we did the welfare reform thing in the proper way.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I think of the man who grabbed me by the shoulder once with tears in his eyes and said his daughter was dying of cancer and he thanked me for giving him a chance to spend some time with her without losing his job because of the Family and Medical Leave Act.
Speech: I think of the man who grabbed me by the shoulder once with tears in his eyes and said his daughter was dying of cancer and he thanked me for giving him a chance to spend some time with her without losing his job because of the Family and Medical Leave Act.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: I think of all the people I grew up with and went to school with and who I stay in touch with and who nerve let me forget how what we do in Washington affects all of you out there in America.
Speech: I think of all the people I grew up with and went to school with and who I stay in touch with and who nerve let me forget how what we do in Washington affects all of you out there in America.
Speaker: CLINTON
Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: Folks, we can build that bridge to the 21st Century, big enough and strong enough for all of us to walk across, and I hope you will help me build it.
Speech: Folks, we can build that bridge to the 21st Century, big enough and strong enough for all of us to walk across, and I hope you will help me build it.

Name: William(Bill) J. Clinton

Text: DOLE: Thank you, Jim; thank you, Mr. President; thank everyone for watching and listening.
Speech: Thank you, Jim; thank you, Mr. President; thank everyone for watching and listening.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I want to address my remarks to the young people of America, because they're the ones that are going to spend most of their life in the 21st Century.
Speech: I want to address my remarks to the young people of America, because they're the ones that are going to spend most of their life in the 21st Century.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: They're the ones who have the challenges and they are people out there making predictions that it's not going to be the same.
Speech: They're the ones who have the challenges and they are people out there making predictions that it's not going to be the same.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: You're not going to have the opportunities; there are going to be more deficits, more drugs, more crime, and less confidence in the American people.
Speech: You're not going to have the opportunities; there are going to be more deficits, more drugs, more crime, and less confidence in the American people.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: And that's what you're faced with, the parents are faced with, and the grand parents are faced with.
Speech: And that's what you're faced with, the parents are faced with, and the grand parents are faced with.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: It's important, it's their future.
Speech: It's important, it's their future.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Speech: And I would say to those I know there are more young people experimenting with drugs today than ever before; drug use has gone up.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: And if you care about the future of America, if you care about your future, just don't do it.
Speech: And if you care about the future of America, if you care about your future, just don't do it.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: And I know that I'm someone older than you.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: But I've had my anxious moments in my life.
Speech: But I've had my anxious moments in my life.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Speech: I've learned to feed myself and to walk and to dress.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I'm standing here as proof that in America the possibilities are unlimited.
Speech: I'm standing here as proof that in America the possibilities are unlimited.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: I know who I am, and I know where I'm from, and I know where I want to take America.
Speech: I know who I am, and I know where I'm from, and I know where I want to take America.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: We are the greatest country on the face of the earth.
Speech: We are the greatest country on the face of the earth.

Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: We do more good things for more people in our communities, our neighborhoods, than anywhere that I know of.
Speech: We do more good things for more people in our communities, our neighborhoods, than anywhere that I know of.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Text: This election is important.
Speech: This election is important.
Speaker: DOLE
Name: Robert J. Dole

Speech: I ask for your support, I ask for your help.
